ormans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":5,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":14,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":49,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Wyham was born in 1210, in England, his father, Ralph de Wyham, was 27 and his mother, Mrs Ralph de Wyhum, was 26. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs William de Wyham."},"et":{"1210–":"1210–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1212–Female":"1212–Surnud","1243–1289":"1243–1289","1183–Male":"1183–Surnud","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1289":"1289","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1243":"1243","1185":"1185","1183":"1183","England":"England"},"fi":{"1210–":"1210–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1212–Female":"1212–Kuollut","1243–1289":"1243–1289